# Changelog

This project uses **[Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/)** style in **`CHANGELOG.md`**.

## Unreleased vs a versioned release

- **`## [Unreleased]`** is a **draft** bucket: new bullets go here **while** work is in progress on the branch.
- **`## [x.y.z] — date`** is what **users and git tags** refer to. Nothing that ships in a release should stay only under **`[Unreleased]`** once that release is cut.

If the user asks to **release**, **ship**, **cut a version**, or **publish a version**, treat the changelog as **incomplete** until the **Cutting a release** steps below are done for that version. Do **not** leave shipped features documented only under **`[Unreleased]`**.

## When to edit

- After **user-visible** changes (UI, exports, flags, GTFS behaviour, env vars, docs that ship with the app): add bullets under **`## [Unreleased]`** in the right subsection (**Added** / **Changed** / **Fixed** / **Removed**).
- **Internal-only** refactors with no behaviour change: usually omit, unless it affects maintainers.

## How to write entries

- **Past tense**, one idea per bullet, link issues/PRs only if the repo already uses them.
- Do **not** duplicate the entire app description; summarize the delta.

## Release date format (Ireland)

- Use **`DD-MM-YYYY`** with **hyphens** in version headings, e.g. **`07-04-2026`** (day–month–year, same idea as common Irish written dates).
- Example: **`## [1.9.0] — 07-04-2026`**

## Cutting a release (required when shipping an update)

Do **all** of these in **`CHANGELOG.md`** for the release to be complete:

1. Move every bullet from **`[Unreleased]`** into a new **`## [x.y.z] — DD-MM-YYYY`** section (follow [SemVer](https://semver.org/) for `x.y.z`; pick the release date in **Irish `DD-MM-YYYY`** or ask if unsure).
2. Reset **`[Unreleased]`** to empty subsection placeholders (**Added** / **Changed** / **Fixed** / **Removed**), not a duplicate of the release.
3. Update the **footer compare links** at the bottom so **`[Unreleased]`** points to **`compare/vx.y.z...HEAD`** and add **`[x.y.z]`** with a sensible `compare` range (see existing links).

Remind the user to create a matching **git tag** **`vx.y.z`** when they publish (or note it in the release PR), unless they say not to.

## Anti-patterns

- Leaving **`[Unreleased]`** empty while shipping features in the same branch for a long time.
- **Shipping a release** while user-visible bullets still sit only under **`[Unreleased]`** (forgot to move them into **`[x.y.z]`**).
- Version bumps in `CHANGELOG.md` without a matching **git tag** `vx.y.z` when you actually release.
